4. Log Review Process
Add a short section “Firewall Log Review”:

All production firewalls/SGs send logs to <logging platform> (e.g., CloudWatch, ELK, Datadog).

Security/DevOps reviews firewall logs at least <monthly/quarterly> for: denied traffic to critical resources, repeated probes, unexpected sources/destinations, and rule misconfigurations.

Significant findings (e.g., repeated blocked attempts, anomalous access) are documented in <ticket system> with remediation steps.

Evidence: screenshots or exports of log dashboards and review tickets during the audit period.

5. Change Management and Justifications
Add a “Firewall Rule Change Process” section:

All new firewall rules or changes require a change ticket in <Jira/Linear> including:

Requester, affected firewall/ruleset, proposed change (source, destination, port, action), business justification, risk assessment, and planned start/end time.

A designated approver (e.g., DevOps Lead or Security Lead) must review and approve changes before implementation, except documented emergencies.

After implementation, changes are tested and documented in the same ticket, including any follow‑up adjustments or rollback.

The firewall ruleset is formally reviewed at least annually, and the review report records: reviewer, date, firewalls covered, rules examined, redundant rules removed, and any high‑risk rules that require exceptions.

